<h1>“Voices from the Past | Voices from the Present” was a workshop with UC Berkeley Professor of Law Khiara M. Bridges on the Supreme Court’s decision to overturn&nbsp;<i>Roe v. Wade</i>. Professor Bridges explored the role of originalism in the Court’s decision, and discussed how originalism privileges the voices of the few who held power centuries ago, while silencing people who live today.</h1><br><br>
